        {
            "id": "https://johnson.wtf/choo-choo/",
            "url": "https://johnson.wtf/choo-choo/",
            "title": "Choo Choo",
            "summary": "I recently went to the Mariners' opening night here in Seattle. It was the first time I've been to a baseball game since game 7&hellip;",
            "content_html": "<figure class=\"post__image\"><img loading=\"lazy\"  src=\"https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/IMG_8960.JPG\" alt=\"A view of T-Mobile Stadium for the Mariners opening game\" width=\"4032\" height=\"3024\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" srcset=\"https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8960-xs.JPG 300w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8960-sm.JPG 480w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8960-md.JPG 749w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8960-xl.JPG 1200w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8960-xxl.JPG 1600w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8960-xxxl.JPG 2560w\"></figure>\n<p>I recently went to the Mariners' opening night here in Seattle. It was the first time I've been to a baseball game since game 7 of the 2001 World Series, when the Diamondbacks beat the Yankees. It was a pretty fantastic time, even for someone who doesn't care much for baseball 😜<br>Afterward, we dipped into the bar at a hotel where my friend stayed for a few cocktails. Post-game and post-drinks, I headed back home, taking the opportunity to snag a late-night snap of the Pioneer Square Link Station. It's my favorite station in town; it's truly a stunning train station.</p>\n<figure class=\"post__image\"><img loading=\"lazy\"  src=\"https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/IMG_8984-3.JPG\" alt=\"The tunnel wall inside Pioneer Square Station\" width=\"2932\" height=\"2199\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" srcset=\"https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8984-3-xs.JPG 300w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8984-3-sm.JPG 480w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8984-3-md.JPG 749w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8984-3-xl.JPG 1200w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8984-3-xxl.JPG 1600w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/responsive/IMG_8984-3-xxxl.JPG 2560w\"></figure>",
            "image": "https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/25/IMG_8984-2.JPG",
            "author": {
                "name": "Jay Johnson"
            },
            "tags": [
            ],
            "date_published": "2024-04-07T18:28:16-07:00",
            "date_modified": "2024-04-07T18:28:16-07:00"
        },
        {
            "id": "https://johnson.wtf/sunny-spring-days-make-me-gush/",
            "url": "https://johnson.wtf/sunny-spring-days-make-me-gush/",
            "title": "Sunny Spring Days Make Me Gush",
            "summary": "This past weekend was sunny and gorgeous, so everyone went out to the UW campus to see the cherry blossoms. The mountain was mountaining, the&hellip;",
            "content_html": "<figure class=\"post__image\"><img loading=\"lazy\"  src=\"https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/24/IMG_8832-xxxl.jpeg\" alt=\"\" width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" srcset=\"https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/24/responsive/IMG_8832-xxxl-xs.jpeg 300w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/24/responsive/IMG_8832-xxxl-sm.jpeg 480w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/24/responsive/IMG_8832-xxxl-md.jpeg 749w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/24/responsive/IMG_8832-xxxl-xl.jpeg 1200w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/24/responsive/IMG_8832-xxxl-xxl.jpeg 1600w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/24/responsive/IMG_8832-xxxl-xxxl.jpeg 2560w\"></figure>\n<p>This past weekend was sunny and gorgeous, so everyone went out to the UW campus to see the cherry blossoms. The mountain was mountaining, the blossoms were blossoming. It's always lovely to see so many people out enjoying the day.</p>",
            "author": {
                "name": "Jay Johnson"
            },
            "tags": [
            ],
            "date_published": "2024-03-22T18:14:00-07:00",
            "date_modified": "2024-04-07T18:14:56-07:00"
        },
        {
            "id": "https://johnson.wtf/seattle-sunsets-stay-stunning/",
            "url": "https://johnson.wtf/seattle-sunsets-stay-stunning/",
            "title": "Seattle Sunsets Stay Stunning",
            "summary": "Almost a year since I moved to Seattle, and the views still don't disappoint. No regrets on the decision to leave Austin for new vistas.",
            "content_html": "<figure class=\"post__image\"><img loading=\"lazy\"  src=\"https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/23/IMG_8288.JPG\" alt=\"\" width=\"4032\" height=\"3024\" sizes=\"(max-width: 2560px) 100vw, 2560px\" srcset=\"https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/23/responsive/IMG_8288-xs.JPG 300w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/23/responsive/IMG_8288-sm.JPG 480w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/23/responsive/IMG_8288-md.JPG 749w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/23/responsive/IMG_8288-xl.JPG 1200w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/23/responsive/IMG_8288-xxl.JPG 1600w ,https://johnson.wtf/media/posts/23/responsive/IMG_8288-xxxl.JPG 2560w\"></figure>\n<p>Almost a year since I moved to Seattle, and the views still don't disappoint. No regrets on the decision to leave Austin for new vistas. Now to find a new job, so I can remain in this lovely place!</p>",
